article.description: — Bryce Harris had 20 points in Howard's 72-61 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday night.
article.headline: Harris scores 20, Howard knocks off Maryland-Eastern Shore 72-61
article.linkText: Harris scores 20, Howard knocks off Maryland-Eastern Shore 72-61
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Bryce Harris had 20 points in Howard's 72-61 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday night. Harris added seven rebounds for the Bison (7-11, 2-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Marcus Dockery scored 17 points and Seth Towns added 12. Troy Hupstead led the way for the Hawks (4-11, 1-2) with 19 points and nine rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
